{"info": {"author": "Peter Krenesky", "author_email": "kreneskyp@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "description": "# Powershovel\n\nPowershovel is a modular task tool written in python3. It is intended to be a\nreplacement for Make, emulating and expanding on some of it's most useful \nfeatures.\n\n\n## Installation\n\n\nTODO: Not in pypi yet but eventually...\n\n``` \npip install powershovel\n```\n\n## Basic Usage\n\n#### Create a task \n\nTasks are created by decorating a python function. The task should be in or \n imported by `shovel.py` in the working directory.\n\n```\nfrom powershovel import task\n\n@task()\ndef my_task(*args, **kwargs):\n    print(args, kwargs)\n```\n\n#### Run a task\n\nArguments and flags are passed as `args` and `kwargs`.\n\n\n```\n$ shovel my_task arg1 arg2 --flag --flag=2\n```\n\n\n## Advanced Usage\n\n* [Tasks](docs/tasks.md)\n* [Config](docs/config.md)\n* [Checks](docs/check.md)\n* [Modules](docs/modules.md)", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/kreneskyp/ixian", "keywords": "tasks,shovel,rake,make,ixian,ix", "license": "Apache License, Version 2.0", "maintainer": "Peter Krenesky", "maintainer_email": "kreneskyp@gmail.com", "name": "ixian", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ixian/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ixian/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/kreneskyp/ixian"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/ixian/0.0.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Task tool with make-like features.", "version": "0.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Powershovel</h1>\n<p>Powershovel is a modular task tool written in python3. It is intended to be a\nreplacement for Make, emulating and expanding on some of it's most useful\nfeatures.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>TODO: Not in pypi yet but eventually...</p>\n<pre><code>pip install powershovel\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Basic Usage</h2>\n<h4>Create a task</h4>\n<p>Tasks are created by decorating a python function. The task should be in or\nimported by <code>shovel.py</code> in the working directory.</p>\n<pre><code>from powershovel import task\n\n@task()\ndef my_task(*args, **kwargs):\n    print(args, kwargs)\n</code></pre>\n<h4>Run a task</h4>\n<p>Arguments and flags are passed as <code>args</code> and <code>kwargs</code>.</p>\n<pre><code>$ shovel my_task arg1 arg2 --flag --flag=2\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Advanced Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"docs/tasks.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tasks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"docs/config.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">Config</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"docs/check.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">Checks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"docs/modules.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">Modules</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7153884, "releases": {"0.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9bd28c46ca57410d39cef72d884dfa3f", "sha256": "844c39ef73d45707238972d1caf33f611508e0c6ab9fb8acf910161bd4f7f799"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "ixian-0.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9bd28c46ca57410d39cef72d884dfa3f", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 10205, "upload_time": "2020-05-01T03:51:50", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-01T03:51:50.673558Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b8/77/c55b217531cc64fc01420d1c790c4a53a53e615b1fa538117e7afe260f6c/ixian-0.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.1.dev194": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f5fb1479920daf5bbdf55085ed2c1a77", "sha256"